<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-29T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-29T07:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 27</seg>
                                </opener>
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.00/10–2951: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting United States Special
                                        Representative in Europe (</hi><persName corresp="#p_RJW1" type="from">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Riddleberger</hi></persName><hi rend="italic">) to the Acting Administrator for Economic
                                        Cooperation (</hi><persName corresp="#p_BRMJ1" type="to">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Bissell</hi></persName><hi rend="italic">)</hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-29T13:00:00+01:00">October 29, 1951—1 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>
                                    <gloss target="#t_Repto1">Repto</gloss> 5428. Personal for
                                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BRMJ1">Bissell</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_PPR1">Porter</persName>, from Tasca and
                                        <persName corresp="#p_GL2">Gordon</persName>. Tasca met
                                    Saturday afternoon with <persName corresp="#p_HPSEL1">Hall
                                        Patch</persName>, Chairman of Executive Committee <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss>, and Sperienburg, Chairman of
                                    Council at official level. Both officials stated time had come
                                    to put real steam behind <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss>
                                    manifesto. Under procedures agreed by Council, <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> will set up high level
                                    working parties on coal, steel, electric power, as well as
                                    agriculture and manpower. Housing will await Secretariat study.
                                    Procedure for manpower is under discussion.</p>
                                <p>Hall-Patch would like to get really high level people on working
                                    party on coal, steel and power. He and Sperienburg are most
                                    anxious to have top level Americans participate. Examples would
                                    be Clarence Randall on steel, <persName>Robert Koenig</persName>
                                    on coal, <persName corresp="#p_WWN1">Walter</persName> [<hi rend="italic">Walker</hi>] Cisler on power.</p>
                                <p>High level working parties are to report to vertical country
                                    committees by November 25 for comment and council December
                                    15.</p>
                                <p>Strongly urge cooperation with <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> on this matter. If you agree, US experts
                                    should come as soon as possible to Paris. [Tasca and <persName corresp="#p_GL2">Gordon</persName>.]</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_RJW1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riddleberger</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>